 tin thing she used to bake in and - twice once week and once another, you know, she would bake. And she would bake this big brown bread as well. She had plenty of baking to do. My it's all hard work, and then - when you cook on the open fire your pans ge
t
 in such a mess and all that you know, you've to sweep all the soot off them sometimes, you know, they get dirty you know. Oh she had a lot to do. I've seen her make girdle - girdle scones on two - the fire has to be clear for that though, your fire has t
o be clear like for the girdle scones you know.
