now. Do you know they were lovely. And - do you know how she used to finish them off? Because you see they were so thick - they were so thick you know and - they would get cooked like top and bottom but sometimes the outsides was - a bit raw, well she use
d
 to get the tongs on a stool in front of the fire and put the songs there, spread them out like that and put - something maybe - put scones - the scones on the top you know, something to keep them up - no, she put them like that you see, to - to get them 
a
ll baked round the edge. And turn them. Yes. That was a good idea wasn't it you know, yes, she did. Yes, that's how she used to finish them off. These great big thick milk scones, but they were - they were delicious. But of course mind you I believe the f
lour was far better than what it is now - oh - I can}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8914751\charrsid1197286 \rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7429624\charrsid1197286  get}{
