g I was fair done, and I just thought about my poor mother, how she did all that, that big washing, yes. And up these great steps up the garden and - it was just the garden - a vegetable garden you know with a little - path, yes. And was all hard work I t
ell you, hanging these great big things out and - I don't - I don't know how - no wonder she died, no wonder. At an early age. Very hard.
