l and - I remember he used to play all sorts of nice things, all by ear you know, and there was one, it was called Napoleons March, I - I could - I can - remember it now you know, oh it was lovely, Napoleons March. No, oh it's - it's lovely. He used to - 
a
nd all the old Scots songs you know he could play. It was - it - it used to pass the time away in the winter evenings you know. Eeh it was lovely. And mother might be mat making. She used to make these - rag - with rags you know. Hooking and - yes, my the
 floor was covered with them. 'Cos of course she had plenty of old clothes you know. Always plenty of old clothes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2116411 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7429624\charrsid1197286 Was there anyone on the family who sang?
