for being good attenders you know and - and winning first prize and that. Plenty of books to read. And then - there was always somebody to give us something. I remember there was a lady, we used to live on a very high hill just above the village you know 
a
nd - do you know, there were two old maids and - do you know - she - she saved a lot of magazines for me and brought them all down to me because there was - Oliver Twist went through those magazines and she brought them all down and - for me to read. And 
that was the first time I read Oliver Twist. Oh I loved it - it was nice.
