is like, a little square - carriage, and we'd all get in - well - she had - she mustn't have had many children because I remember - she wrapped me round in a big shawl and - and - there was - I was - I was dressed underneath but this was to keep me warm y
o
u see, and there was - there was maybe just another one and a baby there, I think there must have just been the three of us there, and she used to go to see her mother you see. In a country place you see. So this man - this man took her like in the - this
 buggy thing, I remember that. That's - that's the only time I was ever in a buggy. We used to call the buggies, I - I think that's the - the name they used to go by,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2116411 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7429624\charrsid1197286 So you used to visit your mother's relations then?
