ss - dressmaking too you know that - and alter things, make - re-make things you know, oh yes, but - like she wasn't a grand hand but all the same - she did, used to make the boys - little boys trousers you know. 'Til they got to be a certain age you know
,
 and - make our dresses and - and we used to wear two - two petticoats under - they were called petticoats in those days you know, well we always - she used to always make them at home, and mind one time she hadn't a machine, but she got a machine - she d
i
d get a machine like, she got one after, and I remember when she got it, that machine, it was what they call a Newhome and it was only six pound ten and you know she could pay it with deferred payments you know, and I think she just - she maybe paid in tw
